<h1>Problem 761 - 2019 RMMSL, C2</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 8</h2>
<p>Fix an integer \(n \ge 2\). A fairy chess piece leopard may move one cell up, or one cell to the right, or one cell diagonally down-left. A leopard is placed onto some cell of a \(3n \times 3n\) chequer board. The leopard makes several moves, never visiting a cell twice, and comes back to the starting cell. Determine the largest possible number of moves the leopard could have made.</p>
